parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension Ball Joint Fitting Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension ball joint fitting can cause the ball joint and lower control arm to separate, leading to a loss of steering control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Clicking sound coming from the front driver and passenger wheels
loss of steering control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair due to Unavailability of Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed repair of the front suspension ball joint fitting can cause the ball joint and lower control arm to separate, leading to a loss of steering control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are unavailable
exceeding a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dim or failing headlights can significantly reduce visibility at night, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Headlights are dim
headlights blow out frequently
low beam headlights are particularly affected
turn signals are brighter than headlights
difficulty seeing the road ahead at night
instruments are difficult to see in daylight and poorly lit at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag sensor can prevent airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning light stays on
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
passengers are advised not to ride in the vehicle due to the risk of serious injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting occupants at risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Receipt of recall notifications
but parts are not available for repair
manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for recall repair
passengers are advised not to ride in the vehicle due to the risk of serious injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
occupants sustain injuries
vehicle is destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause issues with window motors, headlights, and other essential systems, compromising safety and performance.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
stalls while driving
headlights are dim or do not provide adequate visibility
window motors fail
causing windows to get stuck
and difficulty opening or closing doors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motors can cause windows to get stuck, making it difficult or impossible to open or close them, which can be a safety hazard in emergency situations.
symptoms: Windows are difficult to open or close
making a loud sound when trying to operate
and getting stuck in the down position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock/unlock system can cause doors to become stuck or difficult to open, which can be a safety hazard in emergency situations.
symptoms: Doors are difficult to open or close
and may not open at all
requiring the driver to climb over the center console to exit the vehicle.
